                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1021">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/16969.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Conferences are being held today between Mexican Consul Garcia and General Villa
                    regarding surrender of State of Chihuahua and agreement will probably be
                    reached. Danger to Americans much diminished. Villa will probably come to United
                    States taking advantage of your offer of refuge in the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
